WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.290 --> 00:00:04.080
&gt;&gt;Being able to clearly express your thoughts
and participate in discussions is a critical

00:00:04.080 --> 00:00:08.570
aspect of higher education. The connections
you make with peers through these conversations

00:00:08.570 --> 00:00:13.410
will greatly enhance your learning experience.
The Janux platform is designed to make participating

00:00:13.410 --> 00:00:18.930
in group discussions easy and convenient.
Discussions in Janux are open to all course

00:00:18.930 --> 00:00:24.570
participants and allow a free exchange of
ideas and a space for collaboration. To participate

00:00:24.570 --> 00:00:29.460
or initiate discussions sign into your class
and select the discussions tab from the choices

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:35.430
across the top of the screen. This will open a window
that houses discussions and forums. The professor

00:00:35.430 --> 00:00:40.390
or course administrator initiates discussions.
Learners like you are able to initiate new

00:00:40.390 --> 00:00:45.329
topic threads in the forums section. To see
the discussions pertaining to the course select

00:00:45.329 --> 00:00:50.650
discussions below the open discussions heading.
This will open all official topics for the

00:00:50.650 --> 00:00:54.340
course. Click on the heading for the topic
to which you would like to respond and the

00:00:54.340 --> 00:00:59.340
discussion will open. To add your own comment
to the discussion, click on the reply button

00:00:59.340 --> 00:01:04.220
at the bottom of the entry. A blank dialogue
box will appear and you can type your reply

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:10.159
in the blank field. To add emphasis or simply
to make your post stand out use the formatting

00:01:10.159 --> 00:01:15.250
tool located at the bottom of the reply box.
This tool will allow you to add boldface type,

00:01:15.250 --> 00:01:20.870
italicize your text, or add underlines. Next
to the formatting menu is access to the Janux

00:01:20.870 --> 00:01:26.710
whiteboard feature. Clicking this will allow
you to draw or write in many colors. This

00:01:26.710 --> 00:01:31.760
shape feature allows you to add a variety
of geometric shapes in various colors. Plus

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:37.060
you can upload an image from your computer.
If you’d like to start a new thread on a

00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:42.100
topic not covered in the existing course discussions
click on the forum button on the left and

00:01:42.100 --> 00:01:46.729
a new box will appear. Within this box you
will see any previous discussions started

00:01:46.729 --> 00:01:51.830
by your peers. At the top of this box you
will see a new discussion button. Clicking

00:01:51.830 --> 00:01:57.590
this will bring up a blank dialogue box with
a space for a title, tags and a message. Just

00:01:57.590 --> 00:02:03.020
like before you can add boldface, italics,
or underlines to your message. Plus the whiteboard

00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:08.459
is available for illustrations. The Janux
platform also offers a messenger system to

00:02:08.459 --> 00:02:12.730
communicate with individuals from your course
and to set up and participate in study groups

00:02:12.730 --> 00:02:17.749
of your peers. Look at the right side of the
screen. There is a long box with the word

00:02:17.749 --> 00:02:23.279
messenger at the top. You may chat with members
of your contact list live while they are online

00:02:23.279 --> 00:02:28.319
or leave them a message to read and respond
later. Look down at the bottom of the messenger

00:02:28.319 --> 00:02:33.329
box. By clicking the contacts button you will
pull up your list of contacts. To add new

00:02:33.329 --> 00:02:39.469
contacts use the search field at the bottom
of the complete list box. This messenger feature

00:02:39.469 --> 00:02:44.669
will allow you to set up discussion groups
or study groups by selecting desire members.

00:02:44.669 --> 00:02:48.379
Communicating with these groups ensures only
the people you wish to see a message will

00:02:48.379 --> 00:02:54.419
see it. In this video we’ve covered discussions,
forums, and the messenger feature within the

00:02:54.419 --> 00:02:58.989
Janux platform. Spend time with each of these
features in order to maximize your learning

00:02:58.989 --> 00:02:59.730
experience.

